"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904739","Department for Education","false","2018-05-23","<p>The finances of any academy, its governance and academic performance are managed and overseen at trust level. University of Chester Academies Trust (UCAT) is accountable for the effective management of University Academy Warrington. The Financial Notice to Improve (FNtI) issued on 4 May 2018 to the trust enables the Education and Skills Funding Agency to hold the trust to account and sets conditions that the trust must meet. The West Midlands Regional Schools Commissioner continues to work with the trust to strengthen both governance and educational standards.</p><p> </p><p>We are holding the UCAT board to account on a regular basis to assess the support and recovery plans they are putting in place for all their academies. Together with the FNtI, that has been issued, the continued scrutiny and challenge, there is a determined commitment to resolving this situation and improving the outcomes for all pupils.</p>","Stratford-on-Avon","Nadhim Zahawi",,"2018-05-23T13:55:13.107Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904739/answer","Biography information for Nadhim Zahawi","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904739/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904739/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-05-15","University of Chester Academies Trust","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, whether he is taking steps to ensure that University Academy Warrington is effectively managed as a result of reports of its financial problems from the University of Chester Academies Trust; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Helen Jones","Warrington North","Helen Jones","144175"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904740","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-05-21","<p>As public authorities, local authority providers of social housing are subject to the Freedom of Information Act 2000 and we would expect them to respond promptly to all enquiries from Hon. Members.</p><p>Housing associations are private sector bodies. They are not subject to the Freedom of Information Act 2000. It would be inappropriate to single this sector out for instructions on how to respond to enquiries from Hon. Members. However as responsible companies with a social purpose we would expect them to deal promptly to such enquiries.</p><p>The Tenant Involvement and Empowerment Standard within the regulatory framework, requires registered providers to offer a range of ways for tenants to express a complaint and set out clear service standards for responding to complaints, and details of what to do if they are unhappy with the outcome of a complaint. This includes a requirement to deal appropriately with complaints made by advocates - such as Hon. Members acting on behalf of their constituents. Once a tenant has exhausted a registered provider's complaint procedure, the Localism Act 2011 provides for them to escalate the complaint to the housing ombudsman by a designated person. The definition of a designated person includes Hon. Members</p>","South Derbyshire","Mrs Heather Wheeler",,"2018-05-21T15:39:09.543Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904740/answer","Biography information for Mrs Heather Wheeler","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904740/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904740/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-05-15","Social Rented Housing: Correspondence","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, if he will issue guidance to providers of social housing on how they should deal with and respond to enquiries from hon. Members.","false","Biography information for Helen Jones","Warrington North","Helen Jones","144176"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904741","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-05-22","<p>​We have received various reports from NGOs relating to the destruction of mass graves, including Amnesty's latest report on the subject &quot;Criminal cover-up: Iran destroying mass graves of victims of 1988 killings&quot;. We continue to take action with the international community to press for improvements on all human rights issues in Iran. When a new UN Special Rapporteur for human rights in Iran is appointed, we will be calling on Iran to grant them access to the country so they can investigate human rights concerns reported there.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2018-05-22T15:07:12.64Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904741/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904741/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904741/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-05-15","Iran: Capital Punishment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what representations the Government has received from Amnesty International and other NGOs on reports of actions taken by the Iranian authorities to destroy the mass graves of people who were massacred in 1998.","false","Biography information for Sammy Wilson","East Antrim","Sammy Wilson","144250"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904742","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-05-23","<p>The Department does not hold this data.</p>","Esher and Walton","Dominic Raab",,"2018-05-23T14:46:20.207Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904742/answer","Biography information for Dominic Raab","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904742/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904742/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-05-15","Housing: Construction","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, what estimate his Department has made of the proportion of new-build properties purchased by (a) owner-occupiers and (b) buy-to-let landlords in the last 12 months for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Dr Caroline Johnson","Sleaford and North Hykeham","Dr Caroline Johnson","144378"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904743","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-05-23","<p>We are piloting in-cell telephony and basic computers in two prisons – HMP Wayland and HMP Berwyn. No funding has been allocated on the preparation for piloting in-cell digital capabilities in each of the other sites listed in the answer to question 133149.</p><p> </p><p>To deliver the enhanced technical capabilities including in-cell telephony and wing-based computers that allow prisoners to manage their own day to day tasks, the funding allocated is as follows:</p><p> </p><p>For sites with in-cell telephony and wing-based computers: HMP Durham, HMP Wandsworth, HMP Holme House, HMP High Down, HMP Kirklevington Grange and YOI Cookham Wood:</p><p> </p><ul><li>In-cell telephony £10.5m</li><li>Wing based computers (kiosks) £0.9m</li></ul><p> </p><p>For sites with in-cell telephony only: HMP Nottingham, HMP Eastwood Park, HMP Moorland, HMP Chelmsford, HMP Liverpool, HMP Guys Marsh and HMP Exeter.</p><p> </p><ul><li>In-cell telephony £6.0m</li></ul><p> </p><p>The following additional sites will receive in-cell telephony only, once cabling is completed – HMP Leeds, HMP Bristol, HMP Swaleside, HMP Aylesbury and HMP Manchester.</p><p> </p><ul><li>In-cell telephony £3.2m</li></ul>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2018-05-23T16:43:44.25Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904743/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904743/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904743/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-05-15","Prisons: Computers and Telephones","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, pursuant to the Answer of 22 March 2018 to Question 133149, how much funding his Department allocated on the preparation for piloting digital capabilities in each of the other sites listed in that question.","false","Biography information for Richard Burgon","Leeds East","Richard Burgon","144343"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904744","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-05-21","<p>There are already strict product safety laws in place that apply to fridges and to freezers.</p><p>Under the Electrical Equipment (Safety) Regulations, manufacturers must only place safe electrical goods on the market and they must continue to monitor safety in use and to take appropriate action if those products are subsequently identified as being unsafe.</p><p> </p><p>The UK is leading on proposals to enhance the standard for fridges and freezers at an international level.</p><p> </p>","Burton","Andrew Griffiths",,"2018-05-21T13:46:24.377Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904744/answer","Biography information for Andrew Griffiths","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904744/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904744/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-05-15","Domestic Appliances: Safety","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, whether he has plans to raise the minimum legal safety requirements for for (a) fridges and (b) freezers.","false","Biography information for Sir Greg Knight","East Yorkshire","Sir Greg Knight","144214"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904745","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-05-23","<p>The number of Independent Monitoring Board (IMB) members is only recorded from April 2013 onwards and is set out as follows:</p><p> </p><ul><li>April 2013 – 1678</li><li>April 2014 – 1504</li><li>April 2015 – 1385</li><li>April 2016 – 1459</li><li>April 2017 – 1471</li><li>April 2018 – 1394</li></ul><p> </p><p>Historical data on IMB vacancies is not recorded, only the current number of vacancies. The number of IMB vacancies as of 17 May 2018 is 691.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2018-05-23T16:46:23.947Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904745/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904745/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904745/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-05-15","Independent Monitoring Boards","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many Independent Monitoring Board (a) members and (b) vacancies there have been in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Richard Burgon","Leeds East","Richard Burgon","144344"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904746","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-05-22","<p>The Independant Monitoring Board Secretariat does not hold historical data. However, they have confirmed that, as of 21 May 2018, there were no Independent Monitoring Boards with fewer than three members.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2018-05-22T10:53:33.647Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904746/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904746/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904746/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-05-15","Independent Monitoring Boards","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, whether any Independent Monitoring Boards have fewer than three members as of 1 May 2018.","false","Biography information for Richard Burgon","Leeds East","Richard Burgon","144345"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904747","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-05-21","<p>We are unable to provide the data requested, as the expenses records that we have are not able to be broken down by the level of grade of staff.</p>","Bracknell","Dr Phillip Lee",,"2018-05-21T16:02:58.82Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904747/answer","Biography information for Dr Phillip Lee","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904747/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904747/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-05-15","Ministry of Defence: Allowances","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what the cost to the public purse has been of expenses for his Department's staff by grade in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Richard Burgon","Leeds East","Richard Burgon","144346"
