"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904751","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-05-22","<p>In 2017, of those who were remanded in custody at magistrates’ courts, 79% were held in custody by the police until their first court appearance.</p><p> </p><p>However, the custody figures for police remand status and magistrates’ remand status comprise of defendants who were remanded at any point during the process not necessarily at first arrest or first court appearance.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2018-05-22T15:51:11.267Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904751/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904751/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904751/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-05-15","Remand in Custody","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what proportion of people who were remanded on their first appearance appeared in court from police custody in the last twelve months for which data is available.","false","Biography information for Richard Burgon","Leeds East","Richard Burgon","144350"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904752","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-05-22","<p>Her Majesty’s Courts &amp; Tribunals Service (HMCTS) does not hold this information centrally. It could only be obtained at disproportionate cost by examining individual case records.</p>","South East Cambridgeshire","Lucy Frazer",,"2018-05-22T16:57:58.503Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904752/answer","Biography information for Lucy Frazer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904752/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904752/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-05-15","Remand in Custody","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what information the Government holds on the effect of remand decisions in cases where the defendant appears on video either from the police station or from prison.","false","Biography information for Richard Burgon","Leeds East","Richard Burgon","144351"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904753","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-05-23","<p>The Department’s focus is on ensuring access to information relevant to applications for bail at the court stage of the process in order to divert defendants from prison. There is no national performance management reporting of the bail process in prisons. In line with all service provision bail support provision is subject to local performance management and inspection arrangements.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart","144353","2018-05-23T16:41:32.107Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904753/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904753/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904753/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-05-15","Prisoners on Remand: Bail Information Schemes","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what information his Department holds on the proportion of remanded prisoners who receive support from bail information services.","false","Biography information for Richard Burgon","Leeds East","Richard Burgon","144352"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904754","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-05-23","<p>The Department’s focus is on ensuring access to information relevant to applications for bail at the court stage of the process in order to divert defendants from prison. There is no national performance management reporting of the bail process in prisons. In line with all service provision bail support provision is subject to local performance management and inspection arrangements.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart","144352","2018-05-23T16:41:32.167Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904754/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904754/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904754/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-05-15","Prisons: Bail Information Schemes","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what monitoring his Department carries out on the extent and quality of bail information services in prison.","false","Biography information for Richard Burgon","Leeds East","Richard Burgon","144353"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904755","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-05-22","<p>The openness of court proceedings and access to information regarding cases continues to be a critical consideration as we deliver HMCTS reforms. The government is working to ensure there are open justice solutions for cases held by the new digital channels that replicate the existing practices in the courts.</p><p> </p><p>Where appropriate we will continue to ensure access to listings, case statuses and outcomes is maintained.</p>","South East Cambridgeshire","Lucy Frazer",,"2018-05-22T16:48:25.123Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904755/answer","Biography information for Lucy Frazer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904755/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904755/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-05-15","Courts: ICT","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what plans his Department has put in place to ensure that members of the public and journalists are able to access information about cases to at least the same extent that they can at present after the planned extension of digital court hearings.","false","Biography information for Richard Burgon","Leeds East","Richard Burgon","144354"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904756","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-05-23","<p>The Government is committed to maintaining a world-leading legal system and is investing over £1bn to transform our courts and tribunals to create a better, more straightforward, accessible and efficient justice system for all who use and need it.</p><p>There are no plans to publish the business case for the court reform programme. Business cases are used for internal governance purposes within HMCTS and the wider Ministry and are shared with the HM Treasury to assist with funding discussions.</p>","South East Cambridgeshire","Lucy Frazer",,"2018-05-23T16:07:42.81Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904756/answer","Biography information for Lucy Frazer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904756/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904756/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-05-15","Courts: ICT","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, if he will publish the business case for the planned digital courts reform programme redacted as necessary.","false","Biography information for Richard Burgon","Leeds East","Richard Burgon","144355"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904757","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-05-22","<p>As the digital courts reform programme is developed and implemented user research will be conducted with those affected by changes including victims.</p>","South East Cambridgeshire","Lucy Frazer",,"2018-05-22T16:58:10.183Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904757/answer","Biography information for Lucy Frazer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904757/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904757/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-05-15","Courts: ICT","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what research his Department has undertaken or commissioned on the views of victims of crime in respect of the planned digital courts reform programme.","false","Biography information for Richard Burgon","Leeds East","Richard Burgon","144356"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904758","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-05-22","<p>As the digital courts reform programme is developed and implemented user research will be conducted with those affected by changes including witnesses.</p>","South East Cambridgeshire","Lucy Frazer",,"2018-05-22T16:59:00.77Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904758/answer","Biography information for Lucy Frazer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904758/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904758/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-05-15","Courts: ICT","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what research his Department has undertaken or commissioned on the views of witnesses in respect of the planned digital courts reform programme.","false","Biography information for Richard Burgon","Leeds East","Richard Burgon","144357"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904759","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-05-23","<p>The estimate to the public purse given as disproportionate costs in reply to PQ 139567 (To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what the value was of severance packages for prison officers that took voluntary early departure and were subsequently re-recruited since after 2010) was based on the fact that the Ministry of Justice does not hold the information centrally, and would need to commission two independent contracted bodies to look through their records to identify operational staff in Bands 3 to 5 (and the closed world prison officer grades) who have left the service since 2010, to investigate whether a severance package under VEDS was paid and whether they have subsequently returned to service.</p><p> </p><p>Through a combination of our contracted shared service provider and the pension scheme administrator we would need to commission work and information that would then need to be cross checked on an individual basis against various criteria. The cost and time to undertake this work given the MoJ does not hold the information exceeds the Department’s cost limit of £850 for answering parliamentary questions and is therefore disproportionate to the public purse.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2018-05-23T16:47:43.537Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904759/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904759/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904759/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-05-15","Ministry of Justice: Written Questions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, pursuant to the Answer of 10 May 2018 to Question 139567, on prison officers redundancy pay, what estimate his Department made of the cost to the public purse of answering that question.","false","Biography information for Richard Burgon","Leeds East","Richard Burgon","144358"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904760","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-05-21","<p>The information requested could only be obtained at disproportionate cost.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2018-05-21T16:03:15.547Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904760/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904760/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904760/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-05-15","Prison Officers: Redundancy Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what the cost was to the public purse of severance packages paid to prison officers who took voluntary early departure in 2011 and were subsequently re-recruited.","false","Biography information for Richard Burgon","Leeds East","Richard Burgon","144359"
