"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904002","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-05-22","<p>Neither I nor my officials have had any recent discussions on the connection between depression and memory loss.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2018-05-22T11:03:22.297Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904002/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904002/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904002/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-05-14","Mental Illness: Older People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what recent discussions his Department has had and with whom on connections between old age depression and memory loss.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","143769"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904003","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-05-22","<p>​In the financial years from 2009-10 to 2017-18, the Foreign and Commonwealth Office has sold 17 former compounds or offices.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2018-05-22T14:58:39.02Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904003/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904003/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904003/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-05-14","Embassies: Sales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, how many British Embassy sites the Government has sold since 2009.","false","Biography information for Keith Vaz","Leicester East","Keith Vaz","143661"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904005","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-05-17","<p>In recent years the UK has gradually re-established its relations with Iran, reopening the British Embassy in Tehran in 2015 and upgrading to Ambassador-level representation in 2016. Since then we there have been developments in a variety of areas ranging from establishing a UK visa service in Tehran to supporting UK-Iranian trade links. Ministers have also established a regular dialogue which supports engagement on a wide range of challenging issues, including nuclear and regional matters. We committed to upholding the Joint Comprehensive Plan of Action as long as Iran continues to fulfil its commitments under it.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2018-05-17T16:08:23.337Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904005/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904005/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904005/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-05-14","Iran: Foreign Relations","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent steps the Government has taken to improve UK relations with the Islamic Republic of Iran.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","143652"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904006","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-05-22","<p>​My Right Honourable Friend the Prime Minister wrote to the new Malaysian Prime Minister Dr Mahathir Mohamad on 11 May to offer her warmest congratulations on his election and her commitment to work with him on many important bilateral issues. This was a historic result for Malaysian democracy. The British High Commissioner in Malaysia, met with the Prime Minister and offered her congratulations on behalf of Her Majesty's Government. I conveyed my own congratulations via social media. We look forward to working with PM Mahathir and his new Administration on the UK and Malaysia's many shared priorities.</p>","Cities of London and Westminster","Mark Field",,"2018-05-22T15:01:25.337Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904006/answer","Biography information for Mark Field","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904006/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904006/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-05-14","Malaysia: Politics and Government","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what discussions the Government has had with the new Malaysian Prime Minister.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","143770"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904007","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-05-17","<p>Saudi Arabia remains a Foreign and Commonwealth Office human rights priority country. Ministers regularly discuss our concerns on a range of human rights issues with the Saudi Arabian Government.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2018-05-17T16:17:34.97Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904007/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904007/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904007/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-05-14","Saudi Arabia: LGBT People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent representations his Department has made to the Government of Saudi Arabia on the rights of lesbian, gay, bisexual and transgender people in that country.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","143653"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904009","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-05-17","<p>The British Ambassador raised the UK's concerns about the treatment of civilians in Kachin State during the current military offensive in his meeting with the Commander in Chief of Burma's military on 3 May.</p><p>In a statement published on gov.uk on 11 May the Minister of State for Asia and the Pacific expressed concern about the latest military offensive in Kachin and called on the Burmese military to fulfil its duty to respect international humanitarian law, ensure access for humanitarian organisations and allow the 2000 civilians trapped by the fighting to leave to safe areas. He called on all parties to the conflict to cease fighting, protect civilians, and return fully to peace talks.</p>","Cities of London and Westminster","Mark Field",,"2018-05-17T10:15:02.767Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904009/answer","Biography information for Mark Field","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904009/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904009/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-05-14","Burma: Christianity","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, if he will make representations to the Government of Myanmar on recent attacks on Christians in Kachin in that country.","false","Biography information for Mr Gregory Campbell","East Londonderry","Mr Gregory Campbell","143689"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904010","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-05-16","<p>The Human Fertilisation and Embryology Act 1990, as amended in 2008, sets out the time limits and conditions for storing frozen eggs. The Government has no current plans to review this.</p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price",,"2018-05-16T15:36:23.173Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904010/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904010/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904010/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-05-14","In Vitro Fertilisation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what steps his Department is taking to enable women's frozen eggs to be kept for longer periods of time.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","143771"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904011","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-05-22","<p>​In the financial years from 2009-10 to 2017-18, the Foreign and Commonwealth Office has received net sale proceeds amounting to £508.876 million. This includes £425 million received for the sale of the former compound in Bangkok in financial year 2017-18.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2018-05-22T15:00:17.547Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904011/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904011/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904011/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-05-14","Embassies: Sales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, how much has accrued to the public purse from the sale of British Embassy premises since 2010.","false","Biography information for Keith Vaz","Leicester East","Keith Vaz","143662"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904012","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-05-17","<p>In February 2017, the Financial Reporting Council (FRC) announced plans for a comprehensive review of the UK Corporate Governance Code, and delivery of this review implements part of the Government’s wider Corporate Governance Reform package announced in August 2017. The FRC’s public consultation closed on 28 February 2018. Responses are being considered and the FRC is on track to publish an updated Code with supporting guidance in July 2018.</p><p> </p>","Burton","Andrew Griffiths",,"2018-05-17T15:17:21.23Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904012/answer","Biography information for Andrew Griffiths","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904012/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904012/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-05-14","Directors: Codes of Practice","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what the timetable is for the Financial Reporting Council to (a) complete its review and (b) publish an updated version of the UK Corporate Governance Code.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","143650"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904013","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-05-22","<p>Foreign and Commonwealth Office officials have made a number of representations, with likeminded partners, to the World Health Organisation to facilitate Taiwan being an observer at this year's World Health Assembly. The British Government will continue to support Taiwan's participation at the WHA.</p>","Cities of London and Westminster","Mark Field",,"2018-05-22T15:03:28.023Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904013/answer","Biography information for Mark Field","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904013/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904013/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-05-14","Taiwan: World Health Assembly","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what representations his Department has made to the World Health Organisation on Taiwan’s non-participation in the World Health Assembly later this month.","false","Biography information for Mr Nigel Evans","Ribble Valley","Mr Nigel Evans","143672"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904014","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-05-22","<p>Foreign and Commonwealth Office officials have made a number of representations, with likeminded partners, to the World Health Organisation to facilitate Taiwan being an observer at this year's World Health Assembly. The British Government will continue to support Taiwan's participation at the WHA.</p>","Cities of London and Westminster","Mark Field",,"2018-05-22T15:05:29.993Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904014/answer","Biography information for Mark Field","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904014/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904014/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-05-14","Taiwan: World Health Assembly","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, if he will make representations to the Director-General of the World Health Organisation on facilitating Taiwan being an observer at the 2018 World Health Assembly.","false","Biography information for Mr Nigel Evans","Ribble Valley","Mr Nigel Evans","143673"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904016","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-05-22","<p>Data on the number of people diagnosed with shingles, and those who have developed eyesight problems are not held in the format requested.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine","143773","2018-05-22T11:09:33.073Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904016/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904016/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/904016/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-05-14","Shingles","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, how many people have been diagnosed with shingles in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","143772"
